ves after the body dies. sufficient [səˈfɪʃənt] adj. When something is sufficient, you have enough of it. After eating a sufficient amount of food, I left the table. surgery [ˈsəːrdʒərɪ] n. Surgery is medical treatment when the doctor cuts open your body. I needed surgery to repair my leg after the accident. tough [tʌf] adj. If something is tough, it is difficult. The man passed his driving test even though it was very tough. tube [tjuːb] n. A tube is a pipe through which water or air passes. The pile of tubes was going to be put in the ground.
